{
  "name": "ca-infrastructure-speech-chaos-or-cosmos-9cdfb1",
  "title": "IT Infrastructure: Are We Building Chaos or Cosmos? (CA-sponsored infrastructure keynote, 1998)",
  "description": "'IT Infrastructure: Are We Building Chaos or Cosmos?' \u2014 Peter S. Kastner keynote on enterprise IT infrastructure strategy delivered under Computer Associates' sponsorship circa 1998. Frames IT spending as ~3% of revenue with 85% going to ongoing operations and 15% to new applications; distinguishes CEO/CFO/CIO perspectives; argues for consolidating fragmented infrastructure through an 'IT cosmos' architectural program rather than piecemeal ('chaos') procurement.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-19",
